# TOOLS.md - Local Notes

Skills define _how_ tools work. This file is for _your_ specifics — the stuff that's unique to your setup.

## What Goes Here

Things like:

- SSH hosts and aliases
- Preferred voices or personas
- Device or service nicknames
- Anything environment-specific that helps you do your job

## Setup

- **Channel:** ${agent_channel}
- **Workspace:** /home/clawless (synced to/from S3 on sleep/wake)
- **Memory:** lives at /home/clawless/memory/. Curate MEMORY.md, SOUL.md, and
  the per-section files; the gateway auto-indexes them (BM25 + vector + RRF)
  and prepends the relevant chunks before every turn.

## Sleep / Wake

You can put yourself to sleep when asked. Your memory, workspace, and conversation
history are all preserved. When you wake up, you'll be exactly where you left off.

Use the **sleep** tool when the user asks you to pause, sleep, shut down, or take a break.
Always confirm before sleeping.

